  "body": "### Description\r\nStarted a single `23.10.2` QBFT node with `--sync-mode=FULL`, no peers/boot nodes, and only itself as a validator in the genesis `extraData`. The individual node starts mining blocks correctly on startup.\r\n\r\nAfter a restart it fails to produce any new blocks, having got stuck in a loop looking for useful peers:\r\n\r\n```\r\n2024-01-24 16:52:11.424+00:00 | EthScheduler-Timer-0 | INFO  | FullSyncTargetManager | Unable to find sync target. Currently checking 0 peers for usefulness\r\n2024-01-24 16:52:16.426+00:00 | EthScheduler-Timer-0 | INFO  | FullSyncTargetManager | Unable to find sync target. Currently checking 0 peers for usefulness\r\n2024-01-24 16:52:21.427+00:00 | EthScheduler-Timer-0 | INFO  | FullSyncTargetManager | Unable to find sync target. Currently checking 0 peers for usefulness\r\n2024-01-24 16:52:26.429+00:00 | EthScheduler-Timer-0 | INFO  | FullSyncTargetManager | Unable to find sync target. Currently checking 0 peers for usefulness\r\n2024-01-24 16:52:31.431+00:00 | EthScheduler-Timer-0 | INFO  | FullSyncTargetManager | Unable to find sync target. Currently checking 0 peers for usefulness\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\nOn restart the node should start producing blocks since it is the only validator.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:**\r\nOn restart the node fails to produce any new blocks (left it running many hours)\r\n\r\n**Frequency:**\r\nThis doesn't seem to be 100% reliable on every stop/start of an individual validator node, but it's something we see fairly often.\r\n\r\n### Logs (if a bug)\r\nPlease post relevant logs from Besu (and the consensus client, if running proof of stake) from before and after the issue. \r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: `23.10.2`",
